fws_master
Class Slave

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      fws_master.Slave
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class Slave
extends java.lang.Thread

A Slave represents a slave. It has a list of Parameters that can be configuration or input parameters. When the thread is started the input parameters are pulled from the slave and saved in a measurements list. The configuration is sent when requested.

Author:
Johannes Kasberger

changeIPAddress

public boolean changeIPAddress(java.lang.String newIP)
If the ip address has changed it's saved after the transfer to the slave. The ip address is converted to two 16 bit values and sent to the old ip address. Afterwards the newIP is saved.

Parameters:
newIP - The ip address of the slave after changing it. Must be unique.
Returns:
false if changing of ip failed
